HEADWORD: Archchancellor
<hw>Arch`chan"cel*lor</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Ger.
<ets>erzkanzler</ets>. See <er>Arch-</er>, <ets>pref</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A chief chancellor; -- an officer in the old German empire, who
presided over the secretaries of the court.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

